12/03/2009
BERLIN, Germany -- A Croat and a Turk are reportedly among the victims of the shooting spree by a German teenager at his former school in the town of Winnenden on Wednesday (March 11th), which left 16 people dead.
The Croatian Foreign Ministry confirmed that Denis Puljic, 37, nephew of Bosnian Archbishop Vinko Puljic, is the Croatian victim in question.
Turkish media reported that a 15-year-old Turkish student, Ibrahim Halay, was also killed.
(Hurriyet, NTV, Javno, Worldbulletin - 12/03/09)
